sub_title: SparkOptimus Founder & Managing Partner, Award-winning author of Disruption In Action, Speaker, Board member. Helping leaders use tech to create disruptive value, human-centric & sustainable by design
summary:
•	𝗖𝗼-𝗳𝗼𝘂𝗻𝗱𝗲𝗿 of SparkOptimus – together with Tom Voskes – where since 2010 we’ve been helping business leaders unlock the power of disruption,  clarifying what needs to be done as well as how to do it
•	𝗖𝗼-𝗮𝘂𝘁𝗵𝗼𝗿 of “Make Disruption Work: a CEO handbook for digital transformation” in which we captured our experience in transforming some of the biggest companies in the world – proving that disruption needn’t be a threat, but instead a power that’s in your hands
•	𝗘𝗻𝘁𝗿𝗲𝗽𝗿𝗲𝗻𝗲𝘂𝗿 with 25+ years of international experience in turning digital transformation and disruption into inspiring success stories 
•	𝗔𝗱𝘃𝗼𝗰𝗮𝘁𝗲 of a future in which leaders and their organizations will use new technologies to create disruptive value, that is human-centric and sustainable by design, improving the lives of people and their surroundings
•	𝗞𝗲𝘆𝗻𝗼𝘁𝗲 𝘀𝗽𝗲𝗮𝗸𝗲𝗿 at large conferences, such as the World Summit AI and the global #1 tech conference CES in Amsterdam and Las Vegas  
•	𝗖𝗼-𝗵𝗼𝘀𝘁 of radio show “BNR Zakendoen” as business partner
•	𝗦𝗽𝗲𝗮𝗸𝗲𝗿 at executive programs of business schools, such as “Technology for boards” at Nyenrode 
•	𝗘𝘀𝘁𝗮𝗯𝗹𝗶𝘀𝗵𝗲𝗱 𝗻𝗮𝗺𝗲 in influential lists of successful female entrepreneurs, such as TheNextWomen 100 and Inspiring Fifty
•	𝗕𝗼𝗮𝗿𝗱 𝗺𝗲𝗺𝗯𝗲𝗿 at non-profit organizations, such as the Royal Concertgebouw Orchestra
 and Stichting de Volkskrant 

“𝐼 𝑎𝑏𝑠𝑜𝑙𝑢𝑡𝑒𝑙𝑦 𝑙𝑜𝑣𝑒 𝑠𝑝𝑎𝑟𝑘𝑖𝑛𝑔 𝑎𝑛𝑑 𝑠𝑐𝑎𝑙𝑖𝑛𝑔 𝑡𝑟𝑎𝑛𝑠𝑓𝑜𝑟𝑚𝑎𝑡𝑖𝑜𝑛𝑎𝑙 𝑖𝑛𝑖𝑡𝑖𝑎𝑡𝑖𝑣𝑒𝑠 𝑡𝑜 𝑎𝑐ℎ𝑖𝑒𝑣𝑒 𝑐𝑜𝑛𝑐𝑟𝑒𝑡𝑒 𝑟𝑒𝑠𝑢𝑙𝑡𝑠 𝑓𝑜𝑟 – 𝑎𝑛𝑑 𝑡𝑜𝑔𝑒𝑡ℎ𝑒𝑟 𝑤𝑖𝑡ℎ – 𝑜𝑢𝑟 𝑐𝑙𝑖𝑒𝑛𝑡𝑠. 𝑇ℎ𝑒 𝑢𝑛𝑖𝑞𝑢𝑒 𝑐𝑜𝑚𝑏𝑖𝑛𝑎𝑡𝑖𝑜𝑛 𝑜𝑓 𝑖𝑛𝑡𝑒𝑙𝑙𝑖𝑔𝑒𝑛𝑐𝑒, 𝑑𝑒𝑑𝑖𝑐𝑎𝑡𝑖𝑜𝑛 𝑎𝑛𝑑 𝑝𝑙𝑎𝑦𝑓𝑢𝑙𝑛𝑒𝑠𝑠 𝑜𝑓 𝑜𝑢𝑟 𝑤𝑜𝑟𝑘-𝑓𝑎𝑚𝑖𝑙𝑦 𝑔𝑖𝑣𝑒𝑠 𝑟𝑖𝑠𝑒 𝑡𝑜 𝑎𝑛 𝑒𝑛𝑒𝑟𝑔𝑦 𝑎𝑛𝑑 𝑑𝑟𝑖𝑣𝑒 𝑡ℎ𝑎𝑡 𝑖𝑠 𝑝𝑢𝑟𝑒 𝑚𝑎𝑔𝑖𝑐.”
